{
  "texts": [
    "First, the layer's weights are transformed into the frequency domain using DHT, and the top frequencies, based on energy, are selected for fine-tuning, while the remaining frequencies are randomly chosen and kept frozen.",
    "The trainable spectral coefficients are initialized using Kaiming initialization, and during backpropagation, only the selected frequencies have their gradients updated.",
    "The inverse DHT is then applied to these updated spectral coefficients, scaled by a factor α, to obtain the transformed weights in the spatial domain.",
    "These updates are merged with the original pretrained weights, resulting in the final transformed tensor.",
    "This approach ensures that only the most informative frequency components are fine-tuned, significantly reducing the number of trainable parameters while maintaining model performance."
  ]
}